-- Indiabulls Financial Group Said to Plan 10 Billion Rupee Sale of Bonds
-- Suprotip Ghosh
-- 2010-07-06T07:29:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/indiabulls-financial-group-said-to-plan-10-billion-rupee-sale-of-bonds.html

          
          
             Indiabulls Financial Services Ltd. 
plans to sell 10 billion rupees ($214 million) of three-year
bonds, according to two people familiar with the issue.  
 Axis Bank Ltd., AK Capital Services Ltd. and ICICI
Securities Primary Dealership Ltd. are arranging the sale, said
the people, who asked not to be named as the plan is private.  
 New Delhi-based Indiabulls told investors it may price the
zero coupon notes to yield 9 percent, one of the people said.  
